<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-iusJ1XwghR0UmhHVkVt6EQ" name="select_components,_nkC7IA9WEd6LqqyVYr5Pow" guid="-iusJ1XwghR0UmhHVkVt6EQ" changeDate="2009-05-28T15:38:34.521-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p> Component selection is the most effective mechanism within the portfolio cycle &#xD;
  to narrow the funnel and eliminate the ideas&amp;nbsp;that cannot be self-sustained &#xD;
  or demonstrate enough value.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p> Conclude&amp;nbsp;the initial triage of all&amp;nbsp;components being considered for &#xD;
  inclusion within the portfolio.&amp;nbsp;Compare all components within a given work &#xD;
  pipeline against the predefined portfolio metrics, measurements, and thresholds &#xD;
  to identify which components meet all of the required parameters and add value &#xD;
  to the portfolio. &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p> These are examples of portfolio metrics, measurements, and targets: &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Business alignment &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Strategic fit&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
      &lt;li> Multiple-criteria scoring models &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Capacity constraints&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Financial &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &#xD;
      &lt;li> &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../practice.mgmt.portfolio_mgmt.base-ibm/guidances/termdefinitions/roi_3DFEBD03.html&quot; guid=&quot;_bQTR0EvAEd6Ona9n0Aj4EA&quot;>Return &#xD;
        on investment (ROI)&lt;/a>, &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../practice.mgmt.portfolio_mgmt.base-ibm/guidances/termdefinitions/irr_30B1CC83.html&quot; guid=&quot;_JYe3gEvHEd6Ona9n0Aj4EA&quot;>internal &#xD;
        rate of return (IRR)&lt;/a>, payback &lt;/li>&#xD;
      &lt;li> &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../practice.mgmt.portfolio_mgmt.base-ibm/guidances/termdefinitions/npv_9E67A924.html&quot; guid=&quot;_jw8zgDNyEd6QsN5bdDcYQg&quot;>Net &#xD;
        present value (NPV)&lt;/a> &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Cost versus benefit analysis&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Technical &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Architectural objectives&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Risk &#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Sensitivity analysis&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
      &lt;li> Monte Carlo simulations &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations>&lt;p> Depending on the size and importance of the component, it might be necessary &#xD;
  at this stage to expand the business justification into a complete business &#xD;
  case. &lt;/p></keyConsiderations>
  <purpose>To identify which components are worth pursuing and which are not.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
